All chapters required by https://github.com/ArcGIS/geosaurus/issues/6846 except for Part 6 are listed here. Part 6 (JupyterLab) does not render maps as expected and hence not to be come with this release.

Notebooks are placed inside `10-mapping-and-visualization-alt` folder. Please feel free to specify a better name if needed. @AtmaMani 

@BP-Ent Can you please do us a big favor by reviewing this guide series? Many thanks!!

This is a new guide for retraining the default Esri Windows and Doors model that is used by the Interactive Object Detection tool in ArcGIS Pro 2.7. The notebook is being shared as a guide instead of a sample because of the additional step requiring unzipping the DLPK.

@rohitgeo can you please review.

Thanks.

while the dlpk support is added now for `from_model()`,
But still, I have kept dlpk related cells, so if the user has an older version of the API, then also the notebook will run.
